Fa'Tima Omran, hello!  Thank you very much for your email.

It is my pleasure to introduce you to Joe Hu, the TIM student who led the P=
erplexity initiative. Thanks to his efforts individuals with active Carleto=
n accounts can access Perplexity for free for a year. Joe is the hero for t=
his initiative.

Joe's answers to your questions are below:

  *
Has this program benefited students in the department? Yes, Perplexity Pro =
has been highly useful for students, particularly for research and source i=
dentification. It saves time by providing AI-powered sourced answers for ac=
ademic and professional inquiries. Over 500 students use it weekly, averagi=
ng 25 queries per user. Feedback has been overwhelmingly positive. I=92ve a=
lso attached a full introduction to Perplexity for reference.

  *   How do students redeem this without being charged? Students simply si=
gn up with their Carleton email and claim the benefit via the 1-year-free b=
anner=97no payment or credit card required.

  *   Are there testimonials from Carleton students or others? As a Carleto=
n student, I=92ve personally benefited greatly from Perplexity, which motiv=
ated me to dedicate time to making this initiative happen, and many peers h=
ave expressed similar sentiments. I can gather testimonials if needed. I al=
so want to thank GSA for their support last month in sharing this program o=
n Instagram and assisting with poster distribution on campus=97it has been =
a big help in raising awareness.

  *   How are personal information and IP concerns addressed? Perplexity en=
sures strict data protection by deidentifying user data and adhering to fra=
meworks like the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework. Users can request data del=
etion, and personal data is removed within 30 days of account deletion. Ful=
l details are outlined in their privacy policy<https://can01.safelinks.prot=
ection.outlook.com/?url=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.perplexity.ai%2Fhub%2Ffaq%2Fwha=
t-data-does-perplexity-collect-about-me%3Ft&data=3D05%7C02%7CBeiqiaoHu%40cm=
ail.carleton.ca%7Cda4a2fa3fa414bedbb9308dd1bb81b37%7C6ad91895de06485ebc51fc=
e126cc8530%7C0%7C0%7C638697199715086980%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1=
hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ=
%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=3D1lSl%2FGgX9fVuhCiE7Eo4IzfI2U8tZPQBbnryEDJuHOw%3=
D&reserved=3D0>.

If you need more information or have more questions, please contact Joe dir=
ectly.

Joe, please meet Fa'Tima Omran who is in charge of Communications for the G=
SA. Please answer her questions if she has additional questions.

Suggest that the communication to graduate students is sent out soon given =
that the claim for the free subscription needs to be made before December 3=
1, 2024.

Please let me know if you need anything else.

Tony B.




